<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SAARC Council of Ministers to Meet in Maldives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The Council of Ministers of
the South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) is to
convene its 19th session in the Maldives on November 29-30, said a
press release issued today by the Kathmandu-based SAARC
Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers or their representatives from SAARC's seven
member countries -- Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the Maldives,
Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka -- will attend the meeting, the
press release said.
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming session will review progress achieved by SAARC
in the area of trade and economic cooperation, including the
transition from the SAARC Preferential Trading Arrangement (SAPTA)
to the SAARC Free Trade Area (SAFTA).
</P>
<P>
The meeting will also examine the recommendations made by SAARC
tourism ministers, environment ministers and experts, the press
release said.
</P>
<P>
Participants will also review the progress made in implementing
the decisions of a SAARC summit held in May in the Maldives,
particularly the establishment of the Group of Eminent Persons
(GEP) and the SAARC Year of Participatory Governance-1997, said
the press release.
</P>
<P>
The GEP is charged with making a comprehensive appraisal of
SAARC, developing a long-range vision and formulating a
perspective plan of action including a SAARC agenda which will
spell out the targets to be achieved by 2020.
</P>
<P>
Other important subjects to be discussed at the session include
the SAARC Visa Exemption Scheme, cooperation with regional and
international organizations and the establishment of a SAARC Human
Resource Development Center in Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the meeting of the Council of Ministers, foreign
secretaries of SAARC member countries will meet on November 27.
</P>
</TEXT>
