<HEADLINE> Azerbaijan Hopes to Integrate with Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Azerbaijan's Foreign Minister
Hassan Hassanov said today that Azerbaijan hopes to join the
Council of Europe (CE). the European Union (EU) and NATO, said
reports reaching here from Baku, capital of Azerbaijan.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the Finnish "Helsingin Sanomat" in Baku, Hassanov
said, Azerbaijan hopes to join the CE in the near future, although
NATO membership may not come as soon for the country.
</P>
<P>
The "western" policies it has chosen have saddened its
neighbors Iran and Russia, he said, nevertheless, as an
independent nation, Azerbaijan will not be affected by any sphere
of influence in its foreign affairs.
</P>
<P>
On Azerbaijan's economic development, Hassanov wishes foreign
countries to increase their investment in its oil industry to help
create job opportunities and achieve prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Without giving up its oriental cultural background, he noted,
Azerbaijan hopes to pipe its crude oil to the West European
markets through Turkey, Georgia and Ukraine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
