<HEADLINE> Iran Against US Move to Disintegrate Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Parliament Speaker Ali
Akbar Nateq Nouri said here today that Tehran is against any move
by the United States to disintegrate Iraq.
</P>
<P>
According to the Iranian official news agency IRNA, Nouri
made the remarks in a meeting with head of Cuban parliamentary
delegation Juan Hererra Machado.
</P>
<P>
He said that Iran supports Iraq's territorial integrity and
independent sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
Nouri said the United States should understand that it cannot
impose its domestic legislation on the international community.
</P>
<P>
Terming the U.S. presence in the Persian Gulf as a threat to
the regional security, Nouri said that the Persian Gulf should
be protected by the regional states and the U.S. and other
foreign forces should be withdrawn from the region.
</P>
<P>
Iran supports peace and security in the Persian Gulf and the
entire world, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the Middle East peace process, Nouri said the
process aimed to destroy the Palestinian nation, adding that "a
lasting peace will be established when the Palestinian nation,
either Muslims, Jews or Christians come together to form a
national government."
</P>
<P>
Describing the relations between Tehran and Havana as
"excellent," Nouri said the two countries have always confronted
the U.S. provocations aimed at undermining the Non-Aligned
Movement (NAM).
</P>
<P>
He called on the NAM member states to exercise coordination
and solidarity to foil the U.S. attempt to weaken the movement.
</P>
<P>
Machado appreciated Iran's support for Cuba in the
international forums, saying that Cuba will always stand by the
Islamic Revolution of Iran.
</P>
<P>
He expressed pleasure with the current political relations
between the two countries and called for further development of
economic cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
