<HEADLINE> Ukraine to Repair Chernobyl Nuclear Power Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine is considering repairing
the ill-fated Chernobyl nuclear power plant as it collected enough
money at a recent fund-raising conference, Ukrainian President
Leonid Kuchma said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here, Kuchma said Ukraine would
invest the funds into building a new shelter over the No. 4
reactor.
</P>
<P>
Blown up in 1986, sending radioactive cloud over a large part
of Europe, the reactor fell out to be the worst nuclear accident
in history.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma disclosed that his country raised 39 million dollars at
the conference held in New York on November 20 with the
participation of over 40 countries.
</P>
<P>
"This sum plus the 300 million dollars pledged by the Group of
Seven industrialized nations and Ukraine's contribution of 50
million dollars is adequate for repairing the reactor," Kuchma
noted.
</P>
<P>
However, international experts estimate that it needs 750
million dollars to repair the entire plant.
</P>
<P>
Participants of the conference realized the Chernobyl
catastrophe is not only a problem for Ukraine or Europe but a
problem for the whole world, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
