<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia to Reorganize Money-Losing Farms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The Russian government is going
to reorganize all the money-losing farms in the next three years,
an expert with the Agricultural Department said today.
</P>
<P>
He said the government will take reform measures according the
specific conditions of these farms, which might include
establishing exterior anti-crisis institutions, merging and
forming agricultural complexes.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the aim of the reform is to establish such
financial and economic institutions that can encourage farmers to
work harder.
</P>
<P>
According to the Agricultural Department, 80 percent of the
Russian farms are losing money. 
</P>
</TEXT>
