<HEADLINE> Fans Clashes after Greek Soccer Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Four soccer fans were ordered
to stand trial Monday for involvement in a post-match melee that
injured seven people.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the end of the match between Ionikos Nikea and
Olympiakos Piraeus, hundreds of supporters from both teams stormed
the field after Olympiakos' 1-0 victory.
</P>
<P>
In the clashes, two Olympiakos players and five civilians were
injured. Police forces intervened belatedly to separate them.
</P>
<P>
Twelve fans were arrested. Four adult men and a minor were
referred to a public prosecutor and the others were released.
</P>
<P>
If they are found guilty, they can get up to one year
imprisonment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
