<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK to Build 30 Jails in 10 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Prison Service said
in its annual report that two or three new prisons will be built
each year for the next 10 years.
</P>
<P>
Local press reports said today that the building program will
provide up to 20,000 new places for the country's rapidly
increasing prison population.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that 30 sites in England and Wales have been
chosen for the projects which will be run by private security
firms.
</P>
<P>
The former Conservative government had estimated that Britain's
jail population, now at 63,500, will amount to 74,500 by 2005.
However, latest forecast said that this figure will be reached
three years earlier in 2002. 
</P>
</TEXT>
