<HEADLINE> Turkish President Visits Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu today met visiting Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel to discuss ways of promoting regional cooperation and
bilateral economic and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu said at a press conference after the meeting
that the two countries shared a traditional friendship and that
Romania appreciated Turkish support to Romanian bid to enter the
NATO.
</P>
<P>
Demirel said in reply that it is instrumental to the regional
stability and security to strengthen cooperation between Turkey
and Romania and among the Black Sea region.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is the fifth largest trading partner of Romania. The two
countries signed a free trade agreement in April.
</P>
<P>
It is the third meeting of the two presidents. Demirel arrived
in Bucharest today for a one-day visit to conclude bilateral
agreements on customs cooperation and cultural exchange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
