<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNCTAD Investment Workshop Starts in Harare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The U.N.conference on trade
and development today opened a five-day regional workshop on
trade and investment diversification here with more than 70
representatives from 13 African countries attending the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will discuss current and emerging global trends on
high-value, income elastic export products of interest to Africa
and Asia, exchange experience on trade and investment, and
facilitate further contacts between African and Asian business
persons.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony, Zimbabwean Minister of Industry and
Commerce Nathan Shamuyarira warned that countries that isolated
themselves risked damaging their economies in the face of
intensified globalisation.
</P>
<P>
''Few, if any, observers of economic development would dispute
the urgent need and necessity of integrating developing economies
into the global economy,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the well-being and prosperity of any country is
highly dependent on the competitiveness of its industries on the
international market.
</P>
<P>
The minister added that knowledge is the key factor for
success and that is the reason for national governments and
international organisations were to place greater emphasis on it.
</P>
<P>
Asia, particularly southeast and east Asia, had over the past
30 years, come to be regarded as the most dynamic region in the
world, Shamuyarira said.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed out that personal contacts and connections,
mutual understanding and confidence are essential if enterprise
networking and linkages are to be a success. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
