<HEADLINE> U.S. F-15 Crashes in Atlantic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 24 (Xinhua) -- A F-15 fighter on a training
mission crashed into the Atlantic Ocean off Virginia Beach this
morning, the U.S. Air Force said.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at 9:45 a.m. EDT (1445 GMT) about 100
kilometers off the coast from Oceana Naval Air Station, where the
plane was based.
</P>
<P>
The pilot told researchers by radio that he was in good condition
and was floating in a raft.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the crash was not immediately known. 
</P>
