<HEADLINE> Japanese Ambassador praises Closer Asian-African </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Many Asian countries are
emerging as development partners for African countries with a
large participation of individual entrepreneurs from both
continents.
</P>
<P>
Japanese ambassador to Zimbabwe Asao Tsukahara made the statement
here at the opening session of a five-day regional workshop on
trade and investment diversification organized by the U.N.
Conference on Trade and Development.
</P>
<P>
"Given the rapid pace of economic liberalization and
globalization, the competitiveness of African countries could be
further enhanced through the maximum use of networking with
counterparts in Asian countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
Networking, he said, is a continuing process of bringing about
personal contacts and connections based on mutual understanding
and trust.
</P>
<P>
He added exports from Africa to Asia had increased
substantially from 1.6 billion U.S. Dollars in 1980 to 4.4
billion U.S. Dollars in 1995.
</P>
<P>
He said, "at the end of the day, I am sure that insights of
the participants will be further deepened into the challenges and
opportunities for Asia-Africa linkages and collaboration through
trade and investment." 
</P>
</TEXT>
