<HEADLINE> UK to Install More Speed Cameras to Reduce Road Accidents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The British government has
decided to deploy more speed cameras in towns and cities
throughout the country to reduce road accidents and deaths, local
press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that speed cameras have cut speeding and
accidents wherever they have been installed, and in west London
fatalities fell by 70 percent over a three-year period.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the number of road deaths in Britain stood at 3,598,
and the government is determined to cut the number and said that
rigid enforcement of urban speed limits is the best way. 
</P>
