<HEADLINE> UNDP Helps Somalia Combat Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Programme (UNDP)'s Emergency Response Division is
contributing 200,000 U.S. dollars to help Somalia combat recent
flooding, a release from UNDP said today.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 1,000 people have died, ten of thousands are
homeless and as many as 200,000 others have been affected by the
disaster.
</P>
<P>
The floods washed out roads and bridges and inundated farmlands
in central and southern Somalia. Food stocks have been destroyed
and large numbers of livestock have perished.
</P>
<P>
The flooding is the worst that Somalia has ever
experienced in 30 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
