<HEADLINE> Lebanese PM Ends Visit to Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese Prime Minister
Rafik Al-Hariri wrapped up his three-day visit to Saudi Arabia
today after holding talks with Saudi leaders on bilateral and
regional issues, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, he held talks with Saudi Crown Prince and deputy
Prime Minister Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz on intensified fighting
between Muslim guerrillas and Israeli soldiers in South Lebanon
and the stalemated Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders stressed that real peace in the region can only
be achieved through returning occupied Arab lands by Israelis.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Saudi Arabia, Al-Hariri also met with Saudi
King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz Sunday and discussed Arab and
international issues of mutual concern as well as bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Fahd renewed the Kingdom's stand in supporting Lebanon and the
UN Security Council resolution number 425 that calls for an
immediate and unconditional Israeli withdrawal from Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed on the Kingdom's support for the
land-for-peace formula in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Al-Hariri briefed Fahd on efforts to rehabilitate public
utilities in Lebanon and reconstruction projects as Saudi Arabia
is the largest Arab country in terms of both supporting
infrastructure projects in Lebanon as well as importing Lebanese
products.  
</P>
