<HEADLINE> Italian President Meets Ethiopian Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Italian
President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro said today that Italy is committed
to furthering the political, economic and social ties with
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Briefing local newsmen following his meeting with Ethiopian
President Negasso Gidada here today, President Scalfaro said
Italy is very close to Ethiopia in its effort to be self
sufficient in food, and will support Ethiopia's measures being
taken to bring about economic progress, democracy and market
liberalization in the country.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Ethiopia will play an important
role in the restoration of peace in the Horn of Africa,
particularly in Somalia, adding that Italy is willing to provide
assistance in this regard.
</P>
