his consultation with President Scalfaro, the first Italian head
of state to visit Ethiopia, as " historic and fruitful".
</P>
<P>
He said he had learned from the deliberation with the visiting
Italian President the desire on the part of the Italian
government and people for a stronger ties between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Italian president also held talks with Ethiopian
Prime Minister Meles Zenawi on bilateral and regional issues.
</P>
<P>
President Scalfaro today laid a wreath at the Victory Monument
here. The Victory Monument was erected to commemorate Ethiopian
patriots who fell in the five-year (1936-1941) resistance
struggle against Italian aggressors. 
