<HEADLINE> ECOWAS Travellers Cheque to Be Launched in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The inauguration of the ECOWAS
travellers cheque is scheduled for December 4 and 5 in Dakar,
Senegal, a senior sub-regional organization official announced
here today.
</P>
<P>
Lansana Kouyate, Executive Secretary of the Economic Community
of West African States (ECOWAS), said the implementation of the
long-awaited project, in which cheques will be denominated in the
west African unit of account, is expected to facilitate financial
transactions in the sub-region.
</P>
<P>
The cheques will be equivalent to 1.376 U.S. Dollars, while
all the banks will post the daily value in local currencies.
</P>
<P>
Kouyate said customs regulations and formalities in the
sub-region had been harmonized to make customs services within
the community to use uniform codes and descriptions following the
adoption of a common nomenclature.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, 14 members of the community have
computerized their systems by adopting the Asycuda software which
will facilitate customs formalities.
</P>
<P>
Talking about the construction of the trans-Sahelian highway,
he said that the 4,460 km trans-Sahelian highway linking Dakar,
Senegal and Ndjamena, Chad was 85 percent completed, while the
Lagos-Nouakchott trans-coastal road was also about 85 percent
ready, he added.
</P>
<P>
The first ECOWAS Tourism Fair aimed at offering a forum for
operators of tourism to familiarize themselves with the
sub-region and promote the inter-community tourism, will be held
in 1998, he said, adding that the harmonization of hotel
classification systems is in progress.  
</P>
</TEXT>
