<HEADLINE> UAE President Arrives in Cairo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, November 24 (Xinhua) -- United Arab Emirates (UAE)
President Sheikh Zayed Bin Sultan Al-Nahyan arrived here this
evening for talks with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak on
breaking the Mideast peace deadlock and boosting bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak greeted his UAE counterpart at the Cairo International
Airport before accompanying him to the Qubba presidential palace
where the UAE head of state will be staying during his two-day
visit.
</P>
<P>
Other key issues they will discuss include the recent crisis
between Iraq and the United Nations and rallying Arab and Islamic
ranks, according to local media reports.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Egyptian TV broadcast today on the
occasion of his visit to Egypt, the UAE leader praised the
strong ties between Egypt and his country as "a model for what
Arab relations should be like."
</P>
<P>
He expressed optimism over the present Arab situation, but he
noted that efforts should be made to "bring us closer to each
other."
</P>
<P>
"If all Arabs had a unified stance vis-a-vis Israel, the
Palestinian cause would have been long solved," he said, calling
on Arabs to stand as one man as they share common interest and a
common destiny.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa said today the talks
between the two leaders will focus on developments in the Arab
region and the Middle East besides the faltering peace
process. Issues related to the Islamic conference to be held in
Tehran in December are also on their agenda.
</P>
<P>
This is the second meeting between the two leaders within a
month as Mubarak visited the UAE on October 31 before heading to
Kuala Lumpur to attend the G-15 summit.
</P>
<P>
The UAE is also a key trade and economic partner to Egypt.
Since it was established in 1978, the Abu Dhabi Development Fund
has pumped 111 million U.S. dollars into various development
projects in Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The UAE is also providing Egypt with financial assistance to
carry out three new irrigation schemes expected to cultivate more
land.
</P>
<P>
In recognition of Sheikh Zayed's contributions to various
agricultural projects nationwide, Egypt has named a giant
irrigation canal under construction in Toshka area after the UAE
leader. 
</P>
