<HEADLINE> Welfare Recipients up to 2.73 Million in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Welfare recipients totalled 2.73
million in Germany at the end of 1996, or 3.3 percent of the
population, up 5 percent from the level a year earlier, showed
official data released today.
</P>
<P>
According to the Wiesbaden-based statistic office, foreigners,
totalling about half a million, accounted for 23.6 percent of all
the people receiving welfare payments, compared to less than 10
percent a decade ago.
</P>
<P>
The number of foreigners drawing benefits increased by 19.7
percent over last year, while that of German nationals was up 1.3
percent.
</P>
<P>
The office said women amounted to 56 percent of all the welfare
recipients.  
</P>
</TEXT>
