tension and resolve the issue, Kouyate said at a new forum here
today.
</P>
<P>
"At the end of the day, the tension would be reduced and
hopefully it would be resolved through the Abuja framework for
peace in Liberia," he added.
</P>
<P>
Kouyate, a Guinean diplomat who once served as the United
Nations assistant secretary-general in charge of political
affairs, came into the current position at the ECOWAS summit last
August. 
