<HEADLINE> UK Foreign Secretary Cook to Visit Central Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 24 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook will visit Hungary, the Czech Republic and Poland later this
week to exchange views with leaders of the three countries on
enlargement of the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
EU countries have agreed to start EU membership talks with
Hungary, the Czech Republic, Poland, Estonia, Slovenia and Cyprus
early next year.
</P>
<P>
During the central European tour from 26 to 28 November, Cook,
whose country is due to take over the EU Presidency early next
year, is expected to underline Britain's support for these
countries bids to join the EU.
</P>
<P>
A Foreign Office spokesman told reporters today: "He (Cook)
will want to explain just how strongly Britain supports
enlargement and how hard it will fight for Central European
interests, such as trade access."
</P>
<P>
"Enlargement is a matter of the greatest historical importance.
We will support it and promote with a maximum effort," the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Labor government has made it clear that it would
launch a standing conference on EU enlargement next February and a
final decision would be made at the EU Summit in Luxembourg next
month.
</P>
<P>
Cook would also explain to his hosts Britain's priorities for
its six-month EU presidency, such as environmental protection,
fighting drug-trafficking and organized crimes, the spokesman
added. 
</P>
