<HEADLINE> French Butchers Call for Renaming of Profession Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 24 (Xinhua) -- France's butchers have called
for the renaming of their title of profession, because the word
"butcher" is now more often used to mean violent killers.
</P>
<P>
In a message addressed to "Ladies and Gentlemen the
journalists," the French Confederation of Butchers said that each
time when massacres, shootings or throat-cutting take place in
reality, the word "butcher" is used to describe the perpetuators
of the crimes.
</P>
<P>
The press uses all the time the word "butcher" to describe
authors of crimes against humanity, the serial killers or tyrants,
and its members feel hurt and offended, said the confederation.
</P>
</TEXT>
