<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Favors Chubais's Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 25 (Xinhua) -- President Boris Yeltsin said
today that he will not kick away First Deputy Prime Minister
Anatoly Chubais, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Meeting Chubais for the first time after stripping his the post
as finance minister, Yeltsin said the story with advances "is not
lawlessness and not the Criminal Code. This is a moral-ethical
problem."
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin praised the first vice-premiers, Chubais and Boris
Nemtsov for their hard working, saying that "the government will
have to reply to many questions" on December 1 when the cabinet
gives an account to him.
</P>
<P>
The president also met with Chief of the general staff of the
Russian armed forces Anatoly Kvashnin and promoted him to the rank
of general.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin commended the certain success in the military reform,
highly assessed Kvashnin's work.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Kvashnin told Yeltsin about the steps taken by
the Defense Ministry for military construction and the forming of
combat ready units of the land forces, the air force and other
services of the armed forces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
