<HEADLINE> Beijing Tibet High School Celebrates Ten-Year Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Tibet High School in the
capital city today celebrated its 10-year anniversary.
</P>
<P>
The boarding school was set up in 1987 in response to the
Central government's call for assistance to the Tibet Autonomous
Region.
</P>
<P>
Located in northern Beijing and a neighbor of the China
Tibetology Research Center, the school covers an area of more than
30,000 square meters and boasts an indoor sports center, a science
and technology building and a standard 400-meter track and field
facility.
</P>
<P>
The school has nearly 700 students divided into seven grades
and 15 classes. Teachers from Tibet are entrusted with the task of
teaching the Tibetan language to students.
</P>
<P>
As many as 480 of the school's graduate students have returned
to Tibet after their graduation from institutions of higher
learning.
</P>
<P>
There are 23 Tibetan classes or schools in China's inland
areas, where there are also more than 150 institutions of higher
learning that enroll Tibetan students. 
</P>
</TEXT>
