<HEADLINE> Russian Delegation Visits Sweden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, November 25 (Xinhua)-- Sweden and Russia are making
preparations for the forthcoming visit to Sweden by Russian
president Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
A Russian delegation, headed by Vice Chairman of the Russian
Security Council Jurij Deriabin, met Swedish Defense Minister
Bjoern von Sydow and Under Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs
Jan Eliasson Monday, newspapers reported today.
</P>
<P>
Deriabin said that the Yeltsin's scheduled visit to Sweden
shows how important Sweden is to Russia and vice versa. He
emphasized that Russia supports the idea of the Baltic Sea region
as a new center of development in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin irked the Baltic countries and Sweden by having
proposed for increased security in Northern Europe and Russia to
provide security guarantees to these countries.
</P>
<P>
Deriabin said that the proposal has been misunderstood.
</P>
<P>
"It is not only about security guarantees but above all about
security-forming measures to reduce tension between Russia and the
Baltic states," he said.
</P>
<P>
On Monday's discussions on the preparations for Yeltsin's
visit, Eliasson said that they had been conducted in a very good
tone.
</P>
<P>
Sweden wished to create a security policy network with Russia
and all the other countries in this region, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
