<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 15 Coffee Plants Closed in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Uganda Coffee Development
Authority (UCDA) has closed 15 coffee plants in Jinja and Kamuli
districts east of the country, The Monitor reported today.
</P>
<P>
These plants are blamed for processing wet coffee for export,
which will affect the coffee quality, the report added.
</P>
<P>
Jamds Juswata, a UCDA technical officer who is in charge of
the operation, said some plants had no licenses for operation,
and some were maize plants which failed to meet the standard for
coffee processing.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, UCDA had closed another 15 coffee plants in Jinja in
the east region and Mukono in central Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Similar operation will continue in other eastern areas,
Luswata added.
</P>
<P>
Coffee is the main export product for Uganda which earns 65
percent of the country's foreign exchange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
