<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HongkongBank to Open Eighth Branch in Interior Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 25 (Xinhua) -- The Hongkong and Shanghai
Banking Corporation Limited (HongkongBank) has received approval
from the People's Bank of China to upgrade its Wuhan
representative office to a branch, HongkongBank's eighth branch in
China's interior area.
</P>
<P>
The Wuhan branch, in Hubei province in central China, will
offer a full range of banking services in foreign currencies and
will also offer trade-related finance and other banking services.
</P>
<P>
Christopher Langley, general manger of HongkongBank, said today
that the bank "is delighted to have the opportunity to contribute
to the progress of Wuhan, which is developing rapidly."
</P>
<P>
The branch in Wuhan will also be the bank's first branch in an
inland province.
</P>
<P>
The other seven branches are in the capital Beijing and major
cities in coastal provinces: Dalian, Tianjin, Qingdao, Shanghai,
Xiamen and Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
Langley said: "In view of the continuing economic development
of the mainland, the Bank is keen to explore opportunities to
provide banking services to both the coastal and inland regions."
</P>
<P>
HongkongBank is one of the note-issuing banks in Hong Kong.
Together with its subsidiaries, the bank has more than 600 offices
in 32 countries and regions in Asia.
</P>
<P>
It is a principal member of the Hongkong Shanghai Banking
Corporation Group which, with more than 5,500 offices in 79
countries and regions and assets in excess of 458 billion
U.S. dollars as at June 30, 1997, is among the world's largest
banking and financial service institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
