<DOCNO> XIE19971125.0090 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Observatory Director Wins Typhoon Committee Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Observatory
Director Lam Hung Kwan today received an award for natural
disaster prevention from the Typhoon Committee of the Economic and
Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific and the World
Meteorological Organization.
</P>
<P>
The ESCAP/WMO Typhoon Committee, a regional body consisting of
13 members from East Asia, opened its 30th annual session here
today, the first ever held in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The ESCAP/WMO Typhoon Committee Natural Disaster Prevention
Award was given to Lam for his "outstanding services and
distinguished contributions" to the Hong Kong Observatory, said
Roman Kintanar, coordinator of the Typhoon Committee Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
The observatory has committed itself for over a hundred years
to natural disaster prevention and promotion of public awareness
and emergency preparedness.
</P>
<P>
In his opening speech, Stephen Ip, secretary for economic
service of the committee, stressed the importance of putting more
resources into mitigating the potential for social disruption and
economic loss associated with typhoons.
</P>
<P>
"The acquisition of a new high-speed computer and a new weather
radar by the Hong Kong Observatory shows that continuing efforts
will be made to upgrade and enhance the forecasting and warning
capability of severe weather," Ip said.
</P>
<P>
Lam said in his speech that Hong Kong and other participating
members had benefited from the free exchange of technology and
experience through the work of the Typhoon Committee.
</P>
<P>
He said Hong Kong would continue to play an active role in the
Typhoon Committee in the years to come.
</P>
<P>
Lam was elected new chairman of the Typhoon Committee at
today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
Meetings of the 30th Typhoon Committee Session are scheduled to
close on Monday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
