<HEADLINE> Shanghai Hosts International Symposium on Enterprise Groups </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 25 (Xinhua) -- More than 160 Chinese and
Japanese entrepreneurs gathered here today to discuss the features
and management of enterprise groups in both countries.
</P>
<P>
Participants exchanged opinions on issues like characteristics
of the Japanese enterprise groups, the relationship between
Japan's economic growth and its enterprise groups, and the
development of enterprise groups in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Economic analysts said that enterprise groups have always been,
and will continue to be, the pillar of the national economy in
Shanghai, China's largest economic and financial city.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics, annual sales of the 54
large enterprise groups on the preferential treatment list of the
Shanghai municipal government now account for more than 40 percent
of the city's overall industrial sales income.
</P>
<P>
Economic experts said these enterprise groups' annual sales are
expected to surpass 5 billion yuan (about 600 million
U.S. dollars) by 2000.
</P>
<P>
Today's symposium was co-sponsored by the State Economic and
Trade Commission and Japan's Mitsubishi Corporation. The Chinese
participants came from Shanghai and Jiangsu, Zhejiang and Anhui
provinces in the developed eastern region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
