today that Singapore will provide humanitarian assistance in the
form of medical supplies to typhoon victims in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Typhoon Linda struck southern Vietnam on November 2 and caused
deaths and extensive damage to infrastructure facilities and
agricultural land.
</P>
<P>
The typhoon was described as the worst to have struck Vietnam
in the past 100 years.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Foreign Ministry said today that the assistance
is being offered in response to the Vietnamese government's
appeal.  
