<HEADLINE> European Respiratory Society Calls for Ban on Tobacco Ads </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, November 25 (Xinhua) -- The European Respiratory
Society (ERS) today called for a ban on tobacco advertising and
promotion, and restriction on smoking in public places.
</P>
<P>
This was contained in a petition from ERS President Professor
Charis Roussos to Padraig Flynn, European Union (EU) commissioner
for social affairs and employment.
</P>
<P>
In the petition, Roussos emphasized the necessity for EU health
ministers to act decisively at the Health Council meeting on
December 4 to approve the ban.
</P>
<P>
He said the huge toll in terms of illnesses and death directly
attributable to smoking was imposing a huge burden on health care
systems.
</P>
<P>
Flynn assured the ERS president of his full support for the
petition and, at the same time, called on the young people, who
are unaware and unappreciative of these dangers, to have
protection against tobacco advertising. 
