<HEADLINE> 19 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Nineteen rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) have been killed in military
operations by the Turkish security forces in southeastern Turkey,
an official statement announced today.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule, said that the government troops had killed 13 PKK militants
in Eruh town of Siirt province, five at Hendek village in Ergani
town of Diyarbakir province and one in Kalasevir region of Bitlis
province.
</P>
<P>
Two security soldiers died in the clashes, the statement said,
without specifying when the battles occurred.
</P>
<P>
One PKK rebel surrendered to the security forces in Ovacik
town of Tunceli province, it added.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 13-year-old separatist war, which
claimed over 28,000 lives in eastern and southeastern Turkey since
August 1984. 
</P>
