<HEADLINE> Congo, Uganda to Cooperate in Fighting Ugandan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, November 25 (Xinhua) -- A Congo security team
concluded its visit to Uganda Monday with a promise to cooperate
with their Ugandan counterparts in fighting against rebels in
west Uganda, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a public meeting in western Bundibugyo district,
the Congolese guests assured their Ugandan audience that Congo
would join them in wiping out the Allied Democratic Forces (ADF).
</P>
<P>
ADF is a rebel group operating in the country's west with some
350 soldiers. It has some hideouts in eastern Congo, reports
claimed.
</P>
<P>
During its four-day tour, the team, led by Sikulu Basakama
Makishi, administrator of Beni town in eastern Congo, paid visit
to Kabarole, Bundibugyo and Kasese districts in western Uganda,
which are harassed by ADF rebels.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant Colonel Charles Angina, operations commander of
Ugandan army in the western part of the country, held talks with
the Congolese team during its visit.
</P>
<P>
According to Angina, it was important for the two countries to
fight insecurity, since there were no development in the region
without peace.
</P>
<P>
Angina visited eastern Congo earlier this year on security
issues in their common border areas. 
</P>
