<HEADLINE> Chinese Senior Military Leader Meets French General Chief of Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 25 (Xinhua) -- General Chi Haotian,
vice-chairman of China's Central Military Commission, said today
that China values its ties with European Union countries and holds
that a prosperous and strong Europe will be conducive to the
world peace and stability in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also Chinese state councillor and national defense
minister, made the remarks in a meeting here this afternoon with
Jean-Philippe Douin, general chief of Staff of the Armed Forces of
France.
</P>
<P>
China and France enjoy a good relationship and ties between the
two armed forces have scored constant and steady growth since
the two countries forged diplomatic relations, Chi said.
</P>
<P>
China is the biggest developing country, while France is a
developed one, and both are permanent members of the UN Security
Council, he said, adding that the establishment of a comprehensive
strategic partnership for the future between the two nations will
not only serve the fundamental interests of the two peoples, but
also benefit the peace and development of the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
He said that the present China visit by Douin would advance the
existing friendly and cooperative ties between the two countries
and the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Douin said that the relations between the two armed forces are
growing steadily. Every French government attaches great
importance to French-China ties, he told Chi.
</P>
<P>
France and China share similar or identical views on many
international issues and the two countries are conducting good
cooperation in various United Nations organizations, Douin said.
</P>
<P>
Douin noted that the current China tour has given him a better
understanding of China. China is a peace-loving country and is
pursuing a defensive policy of defense, thus it will not
constitute a threat to other countries, Douin said.
</P>
<P>
On another occasion today, Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister
Wang Yingfan also met with Douin and his party.  
</P>
