<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Develop Healthy, Stable Ties with Mongolia: CPC Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 25 (Xinhua) -- A senior official of the
Chinese Communist Party (CPC) said here today that China is ready
to make joint effort with Mongolia to develop healthy and stable
ties of friendship and bring such relations into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau
of the CPC Central Committee, made the remark when meeting with
a delegation of the Mongolian Social-Democratic Party led by its
vice-chairman, Sangajav Bayartsogt.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, said China and Mongolia are close neighbors and there
exists profound traditional friendship between the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, he said, the exchanges and cooperation between
the two countries in political, economic, cultural and other areas
have been expanding.
</P>
<P>
Hu noted that the CPC attaches importance to the relations with
major political parties, particularly ruling parties, in China's
neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
The CPC is willing to strengthen the friendly relations with
the Mongolian Social-Democratic Party so as to promote the overall
development of Sino-Mongolian ties on the basis of independence,
equality, mutual respect and mutual non-interference into each
other's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Bayartsogt said his current visit will help promote the
development of the relations between the Social-Democratic Party
and the CPC, as well as the relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He added that Mongolia admires the achievements China has
scored in building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Bayartsogt and his party arrived here yesterday at the
invitation of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
Dai Bingguo, head of the International Department of the CPC
Central Committee, held talks with the delegation yesterday.
</P>
</TEXT>
