<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Sports Doctors Charged in Doping Probe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Two former East German sports
doctors have been charged with physically harming female swimmers
by giving them banned substances, Berlin prosecutors said on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two were named as 55-year-old Bernd Pansold and 58-year-old
Dieter Binus.
</P>
<P>
Pansold was formerly head doctor of Berlin's sports medicine
center. Binus was the swimming section's doctor at SC Dynamo
Berlin, the prosecutors said.
</P>
<P>
The two are held responsible for giving hormones to 19 female
swimmers from Dynamo Berlin between 1975 and 1989.
</P>
<P>
Four coaches who trained female swimmers were officially
charged last month with giving banned anabolic drugs to minors
without telling either them or their parents.
</P>
<P>
The prosecutors said they had given the drugs between 1974 and
1989 with the agreement of the East German sporting authorities.
</P>
</TEXT>
