<HEADLINE> French Carmaker Sells Luxury Vehicles to Saudi Oil Princes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 25 (Xinhua) -- The French automaker Renault has
won a contract from a Saudi transport company to produce 330 Illiade
range luxury buses at a value of 500 million francs (84 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
These vehicles, produced on the model of Renault VI luxury buses,
will be used to transport the personnel of the Saudi oil company
Aramco, said Renault in a communique today.
</P>
