<DOCNO> XIE19971125.0132 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Provides Loan for Indonesia's Poor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 25 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) today approved a 78.6 million U.S. dollar loan to help about
800,000 poor families in rural Indonesia through an
income-generating project.
</P>
<P>
At least 4 million people will benefit from the Rural Income
Generation Project, which will cover 12 provinces where 72 percent
of the country's poor live, the Manila-based ADB said in a news
release today.
</P>
<P>
The project will develop a sustainable mechanism for reducing
poverty through self-help groups and micro-finances services, and
by strengthening institutional and management capacity.
</P>
<P>
A wide range of income-generating activities such as food
peddling, fish fry breeding, hand sewing, small-scale trading,
grass-mat making, brick making and shrimp production will be
encouraged, the ADB said.
</P>
<P>
The loan is repayable over 25 years, including a grace period
of seven years, and carries interest at a rate determined in
accordance with the ADB's pool-based variable lending rate system
for U.S. dollar loans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
