<HEADLINE> HK Customs Officers Seize Suspected Pirated CDs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Customs officers
seized a total of 13,876 suspected pirated compact discs and
arrested seven people today in an anti-piracy raid aimed at
clearing infringing goods from the local retail markets.
</P>
<P>
Officers from the Intellectual Property Investigation Bureau
raided seven shops today. As a result, 7,846 CD-ROMs, 911 music
CDs, 5,119 video CDs, all of suspected infringing nature, were
seized.
</P>
<P>
During the operation code-named "Terminator 21," the officers
also confiscated 3,780 HK dollars (484 U.S. dollars) in cash and
11,500 HK dollars (1,474 U.S. dollars) worth of paraphernalia from
the shops.
</P>
<P>
The seven suspects, six men and a woman aged between 17 and 55,
were later released on bail ranging from 2,000 HK dollars (256
U.S. dollars) to 5,000 HK dollars (641 U.S. dollars), pending
further inquiries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
