<HEADLINE> Eight of Ten World Cup Venues Fencing Free </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 25 (Xinhua) -- At least eight of the 10
stadiums at the soccer World Cup finals will be free of fencing,
organising committee joint chief Michel Platini said here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Platini said at a press conference that the committee would
confirm eight out of 10 stadiums which will not have fencing and
is working on the ninth.
</P>
<P>
Sports minister Marie-George Buffet said the government wants
to stage the tournament without fencing as long as security is
assured.
</P>
<P>
One exception is at Nantes where the city council opposes
dismantling the fencing at its La Beaujoire stadium.
</P>
<P>
No date was given for the removal of fencing at the venues.
</P>
