<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Retail Sales in September Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 25 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong's
retail sales in September has been estimated at 19.5 billion HK
dollars (2.5 billion U.S. dollars), an increase of 6 percent over
the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
After discounting the effect of price changes over the period,
total retail sales rose by 3 percent in volume, according to
provisional figures of retail sales released by the Census and
Statistics Department today.
</P>
<P>
Compared with a year ago, sales of motor vehicles continued to
record a robust increase of 27 percent in value and 28 percent in
volume.
</P>
<P>
Sales of other consumer durable goods also went up
significantly, by 11 percent in value and 12 percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Sales in supermarkets jumped by 6 percent in value, but slid by
2 percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Sales of clothing and footwear rose by 1 percent in value, but
registered a decline of 6 percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Sales in department stores dropped by 4 percent in value and 9
percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, sales of other types of outlets recorded
rises of various magnitudes in both value and volume.
</P>
<P>
They include miscellaneous consumer goods (9 percent in value
and 4 percent in volume); jewelry, watches and clocks and valuable
gifts (2 percent in value and 4 percent in volume); and food,
alcoholic drinks and tobacco (3 percent in value and 2 percent in
volume).
</P>
<P>
Sales of fuels grew by 7 percent in value, but remained
virtually unchanged in volume.
</P>
<P>
Compared with August, total retail sales in September decreased
by 5 percent in both value and volume due to seasonal factors.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
