<HEADLINE> China, Indonesia Call for New International Order </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, November 25 (Xinhua) -- China and Indonesia today
called for establishing a just and new international order.
</P>
<P>
The call was made by Indonesian Vice President Try Sutrisno and
Wang Hanbin, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress of China, at a meeting here.
</P>
<P>
Try appreciated China's foreign policy of opposing hegemonism
and safeguarding world peace.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Indonesia wants to establish a just and
peaceful world order and believed that Indonesia and China could
make greater contributions to world peace through their joint
efforts.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who arrived here Monday for a one-week visit, said China
has been pushing for the establishment of a new international
political and economic order, instead of hegemonism.
</P>
<P>
On the two countries' relations, Try expressed the hope that
the two sides will strengthen their friendly cooperation to
promote the development of their relations.
</P>
<P>
The vice president congratulated the Chinese Communist Party on
its recent 15th congress and on China's achievements in carrying
out reforms and open-door policy.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his satisfaction over the cooperation given by
China in international and Asia-Pacific affairs, especially in the
affairs of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
Wang said China, which always attaches importance to
Sino-Indonesian relations, holds that the friendly ties between
the two countries are not only beneficial to the two sides
themselves, but also conducive to peace and development in Asia.
</P>
<P>
"Both China and Indonesia are pursuing peaceful and friendly
policies, so we have common ground on many issues," he said.
</P>
<P>
Wang added that China is ready to enhance cooperation with
Indonesia and ASEAN in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia is the last leg of Wang's four-nation Southeast Asia
tour, which has taken him to Thailand, Malaysia and Singapore.
</P>
</TEXT>
