<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria, Ukraine on Talks to Upgrade Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria and Ukraine opened
talks on Monday in Abuja to strengthen their bilateral ties,
including upgrading their diplomatic relations to ambassador
level.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian delegation was headed by Jibril Chinade,
permanent secretary to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, while the
Ukrainian side was a four-man group headed by Deputy Foreign
Minister Kosdayintin Grichenko, the highest level of visit ever
by Ukrainian officials.
</P>
<P>
The discussion will focus on the opening of embassies in Abuja
and Kiev and the formalization of draft agreement on trade,
science, technical education, economic co-operation and
investment promotion, according to today's Daily Times.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria's head of state, General Sani Abacha met with
Grichenko before the two sides entered into talks. He agreed that
there is the need for both countries to exchange ambassadors so
as to accelerate the development of their friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, Grichenko delivered a special message
from Ukrainian government to Abacha. He also expressed Ukraine's
desire to co-operate with Nigeria in the fields of trade, steel
and energy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
