<HEADLINE> Jiang Attends Dinner for APEC Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VANCOUVER, Canada, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President
Jiang Zemin today attended a grand dinner party in honor of APEC
leaders by Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien at the British
Columbia Place.
</P>
<P>
At a cocktail party, Jiang exchanged greetings and chatted with
leaders of other APEC member economies. The leaders were then
entertained with a show of equestrian skills of the Royal Canadian
Mounted Police and other performances.
</P>
<P>
In the afternoon, the leaders attended a briefing on the agenda
of the 5th APEC informal leaders' meeting by Chretien, following a
welcome ceremony at Vancouver Trade and Convention Center.
</P>
<P>
Jiang will have a full day's informal meeting with other APEC
leaders Tuesday at the Great Hall of the Museum of Anthropology of
University of British Columbia.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Jiang is expected to propose that APEC
formulate an agenda for science and technology industry
cooperation into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The agenda is designed to promote technical cooperation among
APEC members and step up the industrialized application of
scientific and technological achievements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
