<HEADLINE> Varsity of Lagos Plans to Produce Bread </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's reputed University of
Lagos is to establish a bakery to produce bread at affordable
price for its community and the environs, the Daily Times
reported today.
</P>
<P>
This is part of the efforts aimed at boosting the
institution's revenue base to achieve sufficiency and augment
government subvention, according to Vice-chancellor Jelili
Omotola.
</P>
<P>
"The goal of self-sufficient is not in the procurement of cash
but in the production of text books and journals without which
the university can only succeed in producing half-baked graduates
for the country's labor market," the professor said.
</P>
<P>
Soap-making and water project has already been established to
serve the community, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
