<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Loan for China's Power Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 25 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) today approved a 150 million U.S. dollar loan and technical
assistance for a power transmission project in China.
</P>
<P>
Consumers of electricity in four provinces in northeast China
will benefit from the Northeast Power Transmission Project, the
ADB said in a news release.
</P>
<P>
The project will allow increased power transfers from the
northern part to southern areas of the Northeast Power region
covering the provinces of Heilongjiang, Jilin and Liaoning as well
as the eastern part of Inner Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
The project aims to support enterprise reforms in the power
sector and augment power transmission capacity in the region by
establishing additional 500 kilovolt (KV) transmission facilities
and related 220 KV transmission facilities, it said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
