<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Migrants, Illegal Immigrants Repatriated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 25 (Xinhua) -- A group of 77 Vietnamese
migrants and 27 illegal immigrants left here by air for home this
morning under the Orderly Repatriation Program (ORP).
</P>
<P>
The returnees, including 69 men, 25 women, three boys and seven
girls, arrived in Hong Kong between 1988 and 1997, according to
the Security and Constitutional Affairs Department.
</P>
<P>
The department said the total number of Vietnamese repatriated
on ORP flights has thus reached 11,264 since 1991 when the program
began.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that there are still 3,383 Vietnamese
migrants and illegal immigrants in Hong Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
