<HEADLINE> Mount Hengshan In Southern China Attracting Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Over two million tourists
have visited scenic Hengshan Mountain in China's Hunan
Province so far this year, bringing 34 times the income it brought
ten years ago.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the mountain, which is famous for its natural beauty
and Buddhist culture, attracted 2.3 million tourists.
</P>
<P>
The Nanyue District, where the mountain is located, has
renovated 120 scenic spots since 1984 and has spent over three
million yuan (361,400 US dollars) on a number of new attractions.
</P>
<P>
Over 20 million yuan was raised by a local Buddhist Association
for renovation of the Nanyue Main Temple in 1992.
</P>
<P>
In October, 1995, a cable car costing 30 million yuan that was
funded by the National Tourism Administration of China and
Hongkong and Malaysian investors opened to tourists.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, a Thai citizen of Chinese origin financed a large
amusement park in the White Dragon Pool area on the mountain.
</P>
</TEXT>
