<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, November 25 (Xinhua) -- A helicopter of the Sri Lankan
Air Force crashed in action in the north early this morning,
killing all four persons on board, a military spokesman announced
here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the Bell-212 helicopter fitted with two
machine guns was flying over the area of Vavuniya when it crashed
soon after the pilots descended to an altitude of 500 feet (about
150 meters).
</P>
