<HEADLINE> Li Ruihuan to Visit Viet Nam, New Zealand, Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), will visit Viet Nam, New Zealand and
Australia, said Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Tang Guoqiang
here this afternoon at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Tang announced that at the invitation of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of Viet Nam and the Central Committee of
Viet Nam Fatherland Front, Li Ruihuan, member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the
Chinese Communist Party and CPPCC chairman, will pay an official
goodwill visit to the Socialist Republic of Viet Nam on December
7-10.
</P>
<P>
Tang also announced that at the invitation of the governments
of New Zealand and the Commonwealth of Australia, CPPCC Chairman
Li Ruihuan will pay an official goodwill visit to the
above-mentioned two countries on December 11-20.
</P>
<P>
On the significance of Li's visit, Tang said that during the
visit, Li will meet with leaders of the three countries and
exchange views with them on wide-ranging issues of
common concern.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that Li will be the highest-ranking Chinese
leader to visit Viet Nam this year and his visit will further
promote the development of friendship and cooperation between
the two parties and the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Tang noted that this year is the 25th anniversary of the
establishment of the Sino-New Zealand and Sino-Australian
diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
Tang expressed his belief that the visit to New Zealand and
Australia will play an active role in pushing forward the
development of friendship and cooperation between China and
the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
