<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 7th Sino-Japanese Economic Symposium In Xiamen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, November 25 (Xinhua) -- The 7th Sino-Japanese Economic
Symposium, sponsored by the People's Daily of China and Nihon
Keizai Shimbun (Japanese Economic News), opened today in this port
of China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The symposium's theme is the return of Hong Kong and economic
co-operation between China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen government offices and financial institutions like the
State Planning Commission of China, Bank of China, the Hong Kong
Trade Development Council, Japan's Sakura Bank and C.Itoh &AMP; Co.,
Ltd. have representatives at the two-day symposium.
</P>
<P>
The first symposium of this kind was held in 1984. Experts say
the meeting has played an active role in trade and economic
co-operation between China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume between China and Japan exceeded 60 billion
US dollars last year, and for the fourth consecutive year, Japan
remained China's largest trading partner.  
</P>
</TEXT>
