<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Half US Cent Weaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, November 25 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar lost
more than half a U.S. cent today, pressured down by a slide on the
Japanese stock market that flowed through to other regional
bourses.
</P>
<P>
The currency closed in Sydney at 68.71 U.S. cents, from 69.28
late Monday.
</P>
<P>
The local unit had begun the local trading session in line
relatively steady but quickly headed lower in anticipation of the
reaction of the Japanese stock market to news that one of the
country's big four brokerages had collapsed.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was at 87.72 Japanese yen from 87.90
Monday, and at 1.1956 German marks from 1.2022. 
</P>
