<HEADLINE> Zambian MP arrested for drug trafficking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lusaka, November 25 (Xinhua) -- A Zambian parliament member
together with his son has been arrested in connection with
trafficking in mandrax, Zambia Daily Mail reported today.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Mukutulu Sinyani of Drug Enforcement Commission
(DEC) confirmed here Monday that Patrick Kamata has been arrested
after he was allegedly found in possession of 45 mandrax tablets
with a street value of 18.9 million Kwacha (about 14,500 U.S.
Dollars).
</P>
<P>
"The MP was arrested on November 21, 1997 following a search
at his flat No. 4 Bivex in Chingola as a result of the MP's
request to have his son Patrick Johannes Chomba Kamata searched
for suspected abuse of drugs," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Kamata is jointly charged with his son. The case is before
magistrate court in Chingola in northern Zambia. 
</P>
