<HEADLINE> Rape Cases Drop in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Rape cases have decreased
dramatically in Zambia this year compared to that of last year,
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said here Monday that about 403 cases of rape
were recorded last year while 259 cases have been reported to the
police so far this year.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the fall to the initiative taken by the police
and various non-governmental organizations in the country,
according to today's Zambia Daily Mail.
</P>
<P>
The police are no longer treating rape cases as domestic
issues, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the various non-governmental organizations have
contributed to the decrease of the rape cases by educating women
countrywide on certain issues pertaining to the safety from
rapists. 
</P>
