<HEADLINE> Jiang Encourages Enterprises' Participation in APEC Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VANCOUVER, Canada, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President
Jiang Zemin said today that China supports and encourages the
business circle to participate in the APEC process and contribute
to the economic development of the Asia-Pacific region and the
world at large.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks during a dialogue with representatives
from the APEC Business Advisory Council (ABAC).
</P>
<P>
During the dialogue, Jiang shared with ABAC members four of his
observations on the participation of enterprises in the economic
cooperation of the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Firstly, there should be a market-oriented constructive
partnership between the government and the business sector in
every member economy; secondly, the exchanges and cooperation
between business communities in every member economy should be
further strengthened; thirdly, the participation of business
communities benefits both sides; and fourthly, scientific and
technological cooperation should be an important part of business
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that at Tuesday's informal leaders' meeting he will
propose the APEC formulate an agenda for science and technology
industry cooperation into the 21st century. The agenda is designed
to move forward APEC technical cooperation and step up the
industrial application of science and technology achievements, he
added.
</P>
<P>
On the current financial turmoil in Asia, Jiang said China
takes a positive attitude toward financial cooperation in the
region.
</P>
<P>
The ABAC was established in 1995 to increase business sector
involvement in the APEC. The ABAC has 54 members and reports to
the annual APEC informal leaders' meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
