</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- The ruling Serb Democratic Party took the lead in
the November 22-23 election for the National Assembly of the
Republic of Srpska, winning 32.58 percent of the votes, the Tanjug
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Serb People's Union, headed by President Biljana Plavsic,
came out second with 20.2 percent of the votes, preliminary
statistics from the Election Committee of Srpska showed, based on
50 out of 58 constituencies. The Serb Radical Party was the third
vote-getter with 18.48 percent of the votes, while the Socialist
Party got 12.1 percent of the votes.
</P>
<P>
The final results of the election will be made public by the
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe on December
10. (Bosnia-National Assembly-Election)
</P>
<P>
