<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Writer's Manuscripts to Be Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Manuscripts on the book
"Thoughts" by Ba Jin, one of China's literary pioneers, is to be
soon published here.
</P>
<P>
Ba Jin, chairman of the Chinese Writers Association and one of
the most famous and influential writers in China in the
century, established his fame in the 1920s by criticizing the
evils of the society.
</P>
<P>
His book "Thoughts", which has just been published, tells in
500,000 Chinese characters some of the important events in his
life and his acute observations about the world.
</P>
<P>
Many people in the literary and art circles say that
it would be significant if readers could have a look at Ba's
manuscripts on the book.
</P>
<P>
The munuscripts will be published by the Shanghai Literature
Development Foundation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
