resolving the Kurdish problem, the improvement of relations with
Greece and the adoption of a constructive attitude to the problem
of Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz, who arrived here last Sunday, left for Spain this
morning, where he is scheduled to meet and hold talks with his
Spanish counterpart Jose Maria Aznar on Turkey's membership in the
EU. 
