<HEADLINE> "Black Food" Becoming New Dietary Fad in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Foods like black rice, black
sesame, and dates have begun to appear recently on Chinese dining
tables as a form of nutritional food.
</P>
<P>
At a recent seminar on these dark forms of food in Guangzhou,
the capital of Guangdong Province, experts said that these foods,
which used to be considered disgusting, unlucky, and unclean, are
now being seen as nutritional forms of food.
</P>
<P>
Lai Laizhan, a black food expert at the Ministry of
Agriculture, says that more than ten provinces are selling new
species of dark grain, and 100 factories process 200 types of this
kind of food.
</P>
<P>
He said that traditional monographs on Chinese herbal medicine
and modern scientific research both emphasize the nutritional
value of these foods, which are also popular in Japan and
Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
The Heiwulei (five black grains) Food Group in Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region in southwest China has had good sales in China
and overseas of its black food products, which are expected to
reach 600 million yuan (72.2 million U.S. dollars) this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
