<HEADLINE> Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, November 25 (Xinhua) -- China's cosmetics market
has great potential and experts predict annual sales of 30 billion
yuan by the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
Chinese spending on cosmetics has grown fast in the past few
years, reaching 14 billion yuan last year, 40 percent more than
for 1995.
</P>
<P>
Recent studies have shown that female spending on cosmetics in
major coastal cities is approaching the international levels,
especially in Shanghai, where women spent an average of 88.8 yuan
on skin care and make-up each month.
</P>
<P>
The central government has passed laws and regulations on
the production, marketing, importing and advertising of cosmetics.
</P>
<P>
Products of foreign-funded enterprises in China now have 80
percent of the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
The recent cutting of customs duties from 55 percent to 35
percent will stimulate more internationally-known brands to enter
the Chinese market, industry observers say.
</P>
<P>
Competitiveness will also encourage domestic companies, and the
use of both advanced technology and traditional pure natural
materials for skin protection will make domestic products more
attractive. 
</P>
