<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Border Province Popular With Russian Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, November 25 (Xinhua) -- China's northeastern border
province, Heilongjiang, which shares a 3,000-km border with
Russia, has become a popular resort spot for tourists from
Russia's Far East.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, a record 30,000 people came from that part of Russia
to Heilongjiang, and in the first ten months of this year, the
number of tourists was up 10 percent from that figure.
</P>
<P>
One-day tour services first started in l988 between Heihe city
in Heilongjiang and Blagoveshchensk of Russia. Now, one- or
several-day tours are available between 14 cities in the province
and some Russian cities.
</P>
<P>
Russia is now the largest tourist market for
Heilongjiang. Before the border was open to Russian tourists, the
province was mainly a ski resort for tourists from Japan, Hong
Kong, and Macao.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
