<HEADLINE> Central China Province Building More Irrigation Systems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Henan, one of China's major
agricultural provinces, has more irrigation projects to help make
sure that the year remains disaster-free.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, 200 million work days have been spent
on irrigation projects since September, and 230 million cubic
meters of earth have been moved.
</P>
<P>
The winter water conservation efforts have cost 600 million
yuan, 78 percent more than for the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The province suffered from a serious drought this fall that
affected 3.33 million ha. of land and reduced the amount of grain
by 2.93 billion kg.
</P>
<P>
The local government has called on farmers to join the effort
by building water conservation areas, and the province has added
89,300 ha. of irrigated areas, according to local sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
