<HEADLINE> Results of Bosnian National Assembly Election Released </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The ruling Serb Democratic
Party took the lead in the November 22-23 election for the
National Assembly of the Republic of Srpska, winning 32.58 percent
of the votes, the Tanjug news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Serb People's Union, headed by President Biljana Plavsic,
came out second with 20.2 percent of the votes, preliminary
statistics from the Election Committee of Srpska showed, based on
50 out of 58 constituencies.
</P>
<P>
The Serb Radical Party was the third vote-getter with 18.48
percent of the votes, while the Socialist Party got 12.1 percent
of the votes.
</P>
<P>
The Party of Independent Social Democrats with 3.69 percent of
the votes, and the Coalition aimed at an integrated and democratic
Bosnia and Herzegovina with 1.46 percent, followed behind.
</P>
<P>
Some small parties won about one percent of the votes and were
not entitled to any seat in the 83-seat National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Today's Yugoslavian Vecernje Novosti (Evening Newspaper)
reported the People's Union topped all other parties in Banjaluka
and Prijedor, winning 38.68 and 38 percent of the votes in the two
election districts.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics released by the Election Committee showed
72.18 percent of the 830,000 registered voters went to the polls.
</P>
<P>
The final results of the election will be made public by the
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe on December
10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
