<HEADLINE> Indonesian Minister Elected FAO Independent Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Agriculture
Minister Sjarifuddin Baharsjah has been elected Independent
Chairman of the U.N. Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO)
Council for the 1997/99 period, official sources here said today.
</P>
<P>
"The Independent Chairman has a task to monitor the FAO program
and make sure that it is implemented as well as possible," the
sources quoted Baharsjah as saying Monday after his visit to the
FAO headquarters in Rome, Italy.
</P>
<P>
The Independent Chairman has to monitor the implementation of
FAO programs in 171 countries.
</P>
<P>
The New Director General, he said, has four main agendas:
first, to reduce the number of people who are suffering from food
scarcity to 400 million by the end of the century, from 800
million today; second, to decentralize FAO; third, to implement
the extended agricultural development; and fourth, to increase FAO
efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Every two years, FAO holds a conference during which the
Council holds at least three meetings to monitor the
implementation of FAO programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
