<HEADLINE> OPEC Oil Prices Continue to Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The average price of OPEC's
basket of seven crudes fell to 18.81 U.S. dollars per barrel last
week, 16 cents down from the week before, statistics released
today by the Vienna-based OPEC Secretariat showed.
</P>
<P>
The monthly average price of OPEC oil in October was 19.54
dollars per barrel, while the benchmark price OPEC set is 21
dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
According to the Austrian press agency, Saudi Arabia proposed
that the raising of the oil quota of daily production be discussed
at the coming ministerial meeting of OPEC to be held in Jakarta,
Indonesia's capital.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia's proposal was opposed by some OPEC members, who
are worrying that raising oil quota would cause further drop of
oil prices.
</P>
<P>
OPEC expected that in 1998, the world's average daily demand
for oil would rise to 75.80 million barrels from the 73.48 million
at present. 
</P>
