<HEADLINE> 10 Sri Lankan Sinhala Youths Arrested for Pro-LTTE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Ten Sinhala youths in Sri
Lanka's western coastal areas have been arrested by police for
maintaining close links with the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam
(LTTE) rebels, police sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
Those arrested were living in areas between Kalpitiya, North
Western province, and Negombo, Western province, police said.
</P>
<P>
They had been allegedly engaged in supplying essential goods,
including explosives, to the LTTE. By doing so, they had made a
large sum of money, police said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, another Sinhala youth, Ajith Rohana, had been arrested
on suspicion of having close ties with the LTTE.
</P>
<P>
Police said he even joined the LTTE and got married to a Tamil
girl whom he later deserted.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels are fighting a 14-year-long war with the
majority Sinhala people in a bid to create a Tamil country of
their own in the north and east of Sri Lanka. 
</P>
</TEXT>
