<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Buyer's Market Appearing in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 25 (Xinhua) -- A buyer's market is appearing
in China in the second half of this year, according to a recent
survey by the Chinese Ministry of Internal Trade.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the ministry's Commercial Information Center
show that supplies of 195 major commodities, or 31.8 percent of
the 613 major commodities surveyed, exceed demands in the
second half of this year. The rate is 25.6 percentage points more
than that for the first six months.
</P>
<P>
Supplies and demands are at parity in 408 major commodities that
account for 66.6 percent of the total, down 22.8 percentage points
from the first half.
</P>
<P>
Ministry officials say that the market will not be affected by
a few popular commodities because of the more mature sense of
today's consumers.
</P>
<P>
In addition, manufacturers have been urged to consult studies
when they explore the market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
