<DOCNO> XIE19971125.0258 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Conducts Household Income Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar has launched a
nationwide household income and expenditure survey for the year
1997, according to today's official newspaper The Mirror.
</P>
<P>
The survey conducted by the Central Statistical Organization of
the Ministry of National Planning and Economic Development, which
commenced on November 17, covers 25,470 households in 45 townships
of 14 states and divisions.
</P>
<P>
The move is intended to ascertain household income levels, look
at food and non-food expenditures, and computerize consumer price
index for major cities, the newspaper report said.
</P>
<P>
The survey, which will continue through the end of this month,
is jointly funded by the government and the UNICEF, the report
added.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, per capita national income
increased by 3.9 percent and per capita consumption rose by 0.8
percent in the 1996-97 fiscal year ending March over the previous
fiscal year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
