<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tourism Provides Employment Opportunities in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 25 (Xinhua) -- By the year 2000, China's
fast-growing tourism industry will employ over 20 million people,
directly or indirectly, China Tourism News has reported.
</P>
<P>
This means over seven million jobless people will become
employees in the sector between 1996 and 2000. In 1995, the
industry employed 13 million people.
</P>
<P>
Also by 1996, more than 1.32 million people had been employed
in Chinese hotels, 125,000 in travel agencies, 76,000 in
entertainment, 825,000 in the food business, and 108,500 in the
airline business.
</P>
<P>
It is also estimated that over one million people are employed
in 84 national scenic areas and sites of historical interest.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is one of the fastest growing industries in China, with
50 million overseas visitors and one million US dollars worth of
trade in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
