<HEADLINE> 21 Killed in Highway Accident in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 25 (Xinhua) -- At least 21 people were killed
and 60 others injured in a highway accident in Thailand Monday,
according to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place at about 1 a.m. when two tour buses,
both operated by Nakhonchai Tour Co., collided head-on on a
highway in Phichit province, northern Thailand.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 police and 60 rescue workers rushed to the scene
to help. The injured passengers, including a French tourist, were
taken to nearby hospitals.  
</P>
</TEXT>
