<HEADLINE> Thailand to Attract More US, European Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Thailand hopes to attract more
visitors from the United States, Europe and new markets to make up
for a decline in the number of tourists from Asia, according to
local press today.
</P>
<P>
The economic troubles in Asia have cut the inflow from South
Korea, Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore, Hong Kong, Taiwan and
Japan, the Tourism Authority of Thailand was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The authority saw growth potential in traditional markets of
Europe, especially Britain, and the United States, as well as
Australia, New Zealand and the Middle East. It hoped to attract
more visitors from South Asia, including India.
</P>
<P>
The authority remains firm that tourist arrivals will reach 7.4
million this year compared with 7.19 million arrivals last year.
</P>
<P>
It also expected Thailand to attract eight million tourists
next year, the start of the Amazing Thailand campaign.  
</P>
</TEXT>
