<HEADLINE> Information About China's Mt Taishan Now on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and overseas tourists
can now get information on Mt Taishan, one of China's five sacred
mountains, easily by consulting a tourist service network on the
Internet.
</P>
<P>
Mt Taishan, in central Shandong Province, east China, covers an
area of 426 sq. km. and is 1,545 meters above sea level.
</P>
<P>
It is a major tourist attraction because of its scenery and
cultural relics that include 20 ancient buildings, more than 2,200
stone engravings from various historical periods, and many temples
and frescos.
</P>
<P>
An official in the Mt Taishan Administrative Committee says
that with the network people can get written materials with 900
pictures about accommodations, sightseeing, entertainment, and
shopping on the mountain.
</P>
<P>
Some historical materials about architecture, poetry,
calligraphy, and backgrounds of prominent people related to Mt
Taishan can also be found on the network. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
