<HEADLINE> South China Book Center Attracting More Customers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, November 25 (Xinhua) -- A book center in Shenzhen,
China's earliest special economic zone, in Guangdong Province, has
become an attraction for readers nationwide.
</P>
<P>
It offers 80,000 titles and has on average 25,000 visitors
every day, 10 percent of them from Hong Kong and Macao. And its
sales stand at 300,000 yuan per day.
</P>
<P>
The book center has become China's largest State-run book
store. It was set up in November last year, and plans to
provide additional services like cultural exchange programs and
recreational activities for readers and visitors. 
