<HEADLINE> Plays Attracting New Audience in North Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, November 25 (Xinhua) -- "Thunder Rain", a famous
Chinese play, has been running for more than a dozen nights in the
city of Tianjin, attracting many local drama fans.
</P>
<P>
The play, being performed by the People's Theater of Tianjin,
was one of China's earliest dramatic works by Cao Yu, a leading
playwright of the 1920s.
</P>
<P>
To develop the art form and attract a greater audience, the
46-year old theater company has spent two million yuan on a new
280-seat theater which has a better stage, decorations, make-up
rooms, and seating.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin was an important place of dramatic arts early in the
century. Premier Zhou Enlai and his wife Deng Yingchao were once
active in Tianjin's dramatic performances.
</P>
<P>
The city has nurtured many famous playwrights, directors, and
actors who are now important in theaters nationwide.
</P>
<P>
The theater company will stage a number of well-known Chinese
and foreign classics in addition to "Thunder Rain" in the near
future. The artists believe that the plays and the performances
will be well received. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
