<HEADLINE> Large Optical Cable Project Under Construction in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, November 25 (Xinhua) -- Work has started on a 1,360-km
optical cable project between Huhhot, capital of the Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region, and Xi'an, capital of Shaanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
The cable passes through more than 20 cities and counties and
is a key part of China's national digital telecom network and an
important way for the Chinese government to support development of
the country's central and western areas.
</P>
<P>
The cable will help solve the telecom problems in north and
northwest China, speed up economic and energy development in the
area, and help it open wider to the outside world, said
officials. 
