<HEADLINE> Chinese Polar Expedition Getting Donations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 25 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese South Pole
Expedition has been given a donation of name-brand goods worth 1.5
million yuan by Chinese companies.
</P>
<P>
The goods include washing machines, electric rice-cookers,
electric heaters, microwave ovens, air filters, and
leather-protecting oil.
</P>
<P>
The products were donated by a number of famous Chinese
enterprises in Anhui, Zhejiang, and Jiangsu Provinces, and Samsung
China Ltd. The products are expected to make the living and
working conditions of the explorers better at the South Pole.
</P>
<P>
The team left Shanghai in mid-November to begin China's 14th
scientific survey of the region. 
</P>
