<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine Ready to Send Peacekeepers to Moldova: Kuchma </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine is prepared to send
peacekeeping forces to Moldova if Moldovan leaders make a request,
the Ukrainian News Agency quoted President Leonid Kuchma as saying
today.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian forces would be deployed in Moldova's Dubossar region
to secure the bridge across the Dniester River, Kuchma was quoted
as saying at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma had a telephone conversation with his Moldovan
counterpart Petru Luchinski on November 21, discussing Luchinski's
meeting with Igor Smirnov, the Transdniester leader. Smirnov
asked for the presence of Ukrainian peacekeepers in that region.
</P>
<P>
Citizens in the Transdniester region, mostly ethnic Ukrainians,
hoped to break away from Moldova after this former Soviet republic
declared independence in 1991. A civil war has broken out there,
killing thousands of people.
</P>
<P>
The Russian, Ukrainian, Moldovan and Transdniester leaders met
earlier this year in Moscow and signed a memorandum to end the
civil war. Under the memorandum, Ukrainian peacekeepers will
replace the Russian soldiers presently patrolling the disputed
region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
