<HEADLINE> Sino-Singaporean Airline Co-operation Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 25 (Xinhua) -- The number of flights between
Singapore and China will go from 28 per week to 40 by the year
2000.
</P>
<P>
Airlines in Singapore will fly to nine Chinese cities from the
current seven cities, and travelers will be able to fly to
Singapore from 12 Chinese cities, up from nine. Singapore now has
flights to Beijing, Chengdu, Guangzhou, Kunming, Qingdao,
Shanghai, and Xiamen.
</P>
<P>
Civil aviation administrations of the two countries will soon
sign a co-operative agreement on trade, culture, tourism, and
investment, a source says.
</P>
<P>
Singapore's air carriers are expected to open new flights to
central and western Chinese cities, because of greater investment
from Singapore in the areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
