<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 72,000 Laid-off Workers Find Jobs in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, November 25 (Xinhua) -- 72,000 workers who were
laid off in Shijiazhuang, the capital of north China's Hebei
province, have found jobs with the help of the local government in
the past two years.
</P>
<P>
The local government has offered 3,540 positions to the
unemployed and spent 44 million yuan in re-employment project. The
city's six sectors, including trade, electronics, and textiles
have set up re-employment centers.
</P>
<P>
About 60 percent of the workers have gotten re-employment
training provided by the local government.
</P>
<P>
Shijiazhuang is one of the cities that are experimenting with
restructuring. It is expected that a number of state-owned
enterprises will go bankrupt or be merged.  
</P>
</TEXT>
