<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jansher, Eyles Enter Quarter-finals at Qatar International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DOHA, November 24 (Xinhua) -- World number one Jansher Khan of
Pakistan and new World champion Rodney Eyles of Australia reached
quarter-finals with easy victories in the 100,000 U.S. dollars
Qatar International Squash Championship on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Jansher trounced England's Paul Johnson 15-8, 15-7, 15-7 in 39
minutes while Eyles routed compatroit Billy Haddrell 15-10, 15-9,
15-12 in just 29 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Jansher has captured five Qatar International title and whipped
Eyles in the last three finals.
</P>
<P>
Sixth seeded Ahmed Barada of Egypt lost to Frenchman Julien
Bonetat 10-15, 17-16, 15-12, 7-15, 15-2 in 53 minutes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
