<HEADLINE> New Stone Sculpture Garden Opens in Southeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, November 25 (Xinhua) -- A new stone sculpture garden is
now open to tourists in Hui'an county in east China's Fujian
Province.
</P>
<P>
The 500,000-sq.m. garden has 358 stone sculptures representing
figures from Chinese history, legends, and novels including Hui'an
girls with exotic clothes and Qi Jiguang, a general who fought the
Japanese invaders in the Ming Dynasty.
</P>
<P>
Hui'an is located in a southeastern coastal area in the
province and is known for its granite and for its stone
sculpture. 
