<HEADLINE> Yamaichi's Philippine Branch Suspends Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 25 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine branch of
Japan's Yamaichi Securities Co. Ltd. Monday filed a voluntary
suspension of its operations after its mother firm collapsed.
</P>
<P>
According to an announcement of the Philippine Stock Exchange
(PSE) published here today, with the voluntary suspension of
operations, the PSE is now conducting an audit of the branch's
operations and the eventual transfer of its clients to other
brokerage firms.
</P>
<P>
There is nothing wrong with the Yamaichi branch's operations,
nor any problem involving obligations to clients, the PSE said.
</P>
<P>
However, it said, an audit is still necessary for a voluntary
suspension of operations filed by the branch, which is owned 100
percent by Yamaichi of Japan.
</P>
<P>
Yamaichi is Japan's fourth largest brokerage firm which has
been battered by short-term credit crunch, shrinking business and
high profile scandals.
</P>
<P>
Yamaichi's closure in Japan Monday has been described as the
biggest postwar business failure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
