<HEADLINE> U.S. Dollar Edges Higher Against yen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar finished
slightly higher against the Japanese yen Monday but was barely
changed against the German mark.
</P>
<P>
The closure of Japanese financial markets for a national
holiday and the upcoming Thanksgiving break kept dealings quiet,
after Yamaichi Securities, the No. 4 Japanese brokerage firm,
became the biggest Japanese company to collapse since World War II
and the third financial company to fall in less than a month.
</P>
<P>
The dollar peaked at 127.23 in the early trading, but scaled
back and settled at 126.80 yen, up from 126.40 late Friday. It
also traded at 1.7375 marks, down from 1.7384.
</P>
<P>
Other late dollar rates in New York, compared with late Friday:
1.4053 Swiss francs, down from 1.4085; 5.8162 French francs, down
from 5.8205; 1,702 Italian lire, down from 1,708.58; and 1.4204
Canadian dollars, up from 1.4174.
</P>
<P>
The British pound was quoted at 1.6906 U.S. dollars, down from
1.6932 U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
