</P>
<P>
-- Passive smoking massively increases the risk of babies
developing respiratory illnesses, contributing to tens of
thousands of Australian children suffering asthma, and puts
non-smokers at greater risk of lung cancer and heart disease, an
official report said.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review
</P>
<P>
-- Thirty of Australia's most respected business leaders
yesterday attempted to counter the growing public campaign against
the government's Wik bill with a statement of support calling for
its "essential features" to be passed in the Senate.  
</P>
</TEXT>
