<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IFC Invests $8.2 Mln in Romania's Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) today signed an investment agreement to take an
equity stake of 20 percent for 3.2 million U.S. dollars in
Demirbank Romania.
</P>
<P>
In addition, IFC has also approved a term loan of 5 million
dollars equivalent to Demirbank Romania, which will use the IFC
financing to provide a full range of commercial banking products
including working capital, trade finance, and equipment
acquisition for medium-sized Romanian enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Demirbank Romania is a joint venture bank between IFC,
Demirbank Turkey and a number of Romanian investment funds.
Demirbank Turkey will provide technically trained and experienced
management to the bank. The Romanian investment funds, which have
links to much of the country's corporate sector, will support the
development of the bank's marketing activities.
</P>
<P>
Demirbank Turkey is one of the oldest private banks in the
Turkish banking sector. It has had a long relationship with IFC,
which has arranged two syndicated loans to the bank for a total of
90 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
IFC is a member of the World Bank and also the largest
multilateral source of equity and loan financing for private
sector projects in developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971125.0310 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man Accused of Putting Racial Slur-Covered Cross </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 24 (Xinhua) -- An 18-year-old man
suspected of putting a charred cross studded with racial slurs
outside a museum of black history in Wilberforce, Ohio, was
arrested.
</P>
<P>
Daniel P. Carter, who is white, was charged with ethnic
intimidation, menacing and possessing drug paraphernalia after
officers, including an FBI agent, searched his home early Sunday,
the patrol said.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the National Afro-American Museum and Cultural
Center found the wooden cross Tuesday. It was about five feet tall
with racial slurs, "KKK" and a swastika written on it. No one saw
it burning, but the cross had been soaked with an accelerant and
was slightly charred on the back, the Associated Press reported.
</P>
<P>
The museum, chartered by Congress, opened in 1988 to educate
the public about black history and culture.
</P>
<P>
It is on the old campus of Wilberforce University, 20 miles
east of Dayton.
</P>
<P>
Carter is being held in the Greene County jail. He has no known
link with hate groups, state troopers said. More arrests were
possible, said Lieutenant John Born, spokesman for the highway
patrol. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
