<DOCNO> XIE19971125.0318 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets ROK Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VANCOUVER, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin said today that China is ready to make joint efforts with
the Republic of Korea (ROK) to bring the energetic, healthy and
steady bilateral ties into the next century.
</P>
<P>
At his meeting with ROK President Kim Young Sam here today,
Jiang noted the rapid growth of Sino-ROK political, economic,
trade and other relations since diplomatic relations were
established five years ago.
</P>
<P>
China is satisfied with its fruitful relations with the ROK,
Jiang told Kim.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president also spoke highly of Kim's valuable
contribution to the Sino-ROK friendly neighborhood and the steady
development of bilateral ties, according to Chinese officials.
</P>
<P>
At the turn of the century, China is willing to join the
efforts of the ROK in bringing the energetic, healthy and steady
ties of friendly neighborhood into the new millennium, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The ROK president expressed his agreement and voiced the hope
that ROK-China cooperation in all fields will be further
strengthened.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Kim also congratulated Jiang on China's
success in the diplomatic front, noting the Sino-U.S. summit, the
Russian president's trip to China and the Chinese premier's visit
to Japan.
</P>
<P>
Both agreed that through meetings on various occasions, the two
countries' leaderships have established good working relations,
which have benefited the overall bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also discussed the world financial situation.
</P>
<P>
Briefed by Kim on the ROK's current economic difficulties,
Jiang said that the financial crises in some countries have very
complicated factors.
</P>
<P>
APEC members, and neighboring countries in particular, should
take an attitude of compassion and support, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leader expressed the hope that the ROK government
and people will overcome the temporary economic difficulties.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Jiang also briefed Kim on China's external
relations and its domestic economy.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also exchanged views on issues of mutual
concern.
</P>
</TEXT>
