<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greek PM, UN Envoy on Cyprus Issue Meet in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Greek Prime Minister Costas
Simitis today discussed with U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan's
special envoy on the Cyprus issue, Diego Cordovez, possibilities
of achieving progress in specific aspects of the Cyprus problem.
</P>
<P>
Greek Foreign Minister Theodoros Pangalos held talks Saturday
with Cordovez on the Cyprus issue.
</P>
<P>
Greece is the second stop of Cordovez's three-nation trip which
has already taken him to Cyprus. He will also visit Turkey today.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided since 1974 when Turkish troops invaded
and occupied the northern third of the island. The United Nations
now is doing its best to help the Greek and Turkish Cypriots to
solve their differences. 
</P>
</TEXT>
